    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop medical appointments counting against school attendance",
        "additional_details": "At the moment, hospital and GP appointments during school hours count as authorised absences, but they still lower a child\u2019s attendance record. We believe this is unfair on children with health conditions or disabilities who need regular care. We want the Government to bring in a separate attendance code so medical appointments don\u2019t reduce attendance percentages or make families look like they aren\u2019t supporting education.",
        "background": "We believe children shouldn\u2019t be marked down as absent for hospital or GP appointments. These are authorised absences but still lower attendance records. We urge the Government to create a separate code so medical care doesn\u2019t impact students\u2019 attendance records.",
